            "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://mas.to/@dtiselice\" class=\"u-url mention\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">@<span>dtiselice</span></a></span> That's basically true, although some CO2 is regularly removed from the atmosphere by natural sources (absorption by plants, rocks, and the oceans). That's where the Net Zero idea comes in \u2014 the hope that if human emissions are reduced enough, even if they aren't actually at true zero, the balance will net out to zero. But these natural feedbacks and tipping points we're talking about could invalidate that plan.</p>",
