            "uri": "https://aus.social/users/scottmatter/statuses/112881336699578107",
            "url": "https://aus.social/@scottmatter/112881336699578107",
            "replies_count": 1,
            "reblogs_count": 0,
            "favourites_count": 0,
            "edited_at": null,
            "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://climatejustice.social/@breadandcircuses\" class=\"u-url mention\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">@<span>breadandcircuses</span></a></span> </p><p>Am I misunderstanding the chart or is it entirely likely that the atmospheric CO2 line will cross over the annual emissions line unless we quickly get into drawdown? </p><p>As in, if we flatten annual emissions, as long as we\u2019re still adding more CO2 than is being removed, the amount in the atmosphere will keep increasing. </p><p>Net Zero would stop the increase, but may not reduce concentrations (hence the 1.5C target)</p>",
            "reblog": null,
