            "content": "<p><span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://aus.social/@scottmatter\" class=\"u-url mention\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">@<span>scottmatter</span></a></span> The two lines aren't really connected in the way you suggest. They are shown on the same graph for the purpose of comparison, but are aligned as they are by how the verticle axes are placed. So the orange line easily could have been shown under the dotted line; it's just a choice made by the chart's creator.</p><p>But you're right, if emissions are not quickly and sharply reduced, atmospheric CO\u2082 will continue going up at an exponential pace.</p>",
